                            <comment id="17382099" author="zabetak" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 14:10:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What do we return when input is not a number? Do we throw? If that&apos;ts the case maybe we should throw as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17382178" author="nareshpr" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2021 16:06:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=zabetak&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;zabetak&quot;&gt;zabetak&lt;/a&gt;&#160;We return 0 for invalid input. I can return the same for empty input as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17384268" author="zabetak" created="Tue, 20 Jul 2021 13:47:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nareshpr&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nareshpr&quot;&gt;nareshpr&lt;/a&gt; After having a second look in the PR I kind of change my mind. The CONV function is mostly known from MySQL and I think the implementation so far tends to stay as close to the MySQL version as possible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I did a quick test in MySQL (version 8.0) and it returns the following results:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;mysql&amp;gt; SELECT CONV(&apos;&apos;,10,2);
+---------------+
| CONV(&apos;&apos;,10,2) |
+---------------+
| NULL          |
+---------------+
mysql&amp;gt; SELECT CONV(&apos;4?:+&apos;,10,2);
+-------------------+
| CONV(&apos;4?:+&apos;,10,2) |
+-------------------+
| 100               |
+-------------------+
mysql&amp;gt; SELECT CONV(&apos;1?:+0&apos;,10,2);
+--------------------+
| CONV(&apos;1?:+0&apos;,10,2) |
+--------------------+
| 1                  |
+--------------------+
mysql&amp;gt; SELECT CONV(&apos;*10?:+2&apos;,10,2);
+----------------------+
| CONV(&apos;*10?:+2&apos;,10,2) |
+----------------------+
| 0                    |
+----------------------+
1 row in set, 1 warning (0.00 sec)

Warning (Code 1292): Truncated incorrect DECIMAL value: &apos;*10?:+2&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So for empty string it returns NULL and for invalid literals it tries to kind of parse the literal till it finds an illegal character.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Based on the above I would suggest to return NULL for empty string as you had it initially. Sorry for the back and forth.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17385252" author="nareshpr" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 04:42:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the analysis &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=zabetak&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;zabetak&quot;&gt;zabetak&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I updated PR to return null for empty input.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
